method.name: emulation_ldp_route_config
method.description: This procedure creates/modifies/deletes LSP (FEC) pools or FEC ranges on simulated LDP router Interface.

description.text: Mode that is being performed. All but create require the use of the -handle option. Valid choices are: create - Create a new LDP interface modify - Modify an existing LDP interface delete - Delete the given LDP interface

choice.choiceText: Create the specified LSP or FEC Pools/Ranges.

description.text: The LDP handle.

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.
This argument can be used to specify whether or not the same label will be used for all the FECs in the FEC range. It has any meaning only when the fec_type option is set to host_addr.

choice.choiceText: Next available label is assigned for each LSP.
The same label (increment from previous FEC range) is assigned for all LSPs in this FEC range.

description.text: The first network address in the range of advertising FECs, when fec_type is ipv4_prefix.
Provides step increment for fec_ip_prefix_start for adv Fec Range.
The number of bits in the mask applied to the network address. The masked bits in the First Network address form the address prefix. Valid when fec_type is ipv4_prefix.

Note: this option cannot be modified with modify mode. Valid choices are: ipv4_prefix - configure FECs to be advertised by the simulated router host_addr - configure FECs to be requested of upstream peers, to be used in download on demand advertising mode. vc - configure parameters for VC range associated with an LDP L2 VPN interface.

choice.choiceText: Configure FECs to be advertised by the simulated router.
Configure FECs to be requested of upstream peers, to be used in download on demand advertising mode.
Configure parameters for VC range associated with an LDP L2 VPN interface.
Configure parameters for configuring a network topology.

description.text: If checked, indicates that ATM Transparent Cell Transport mode is being used. Multiple ATM cells may be grouped into a single MPLS frame for transmission from one ATM port connected to another ATM port. Valid only when -mode is create/modify and -fec_vc_type is atm_cell or atm_vcc_1_1 or atm_vpc_1_1 or atm_vcc_n_1 or atm_vpc_n_1 and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.

The Maximum number of ATM Cells which may be concatenated and sent in a single MPLS frame. This parameter is part of the FEC element. Valid only when -mode is create/modify and -fec_vc_type is atm_cell or atm_vcc_1_1 or atm_vpc_1_1 or atm_vcc_n_1 or atm_vpc_n_1 and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.

If checked, sets the C-Bit (flag). It is the highest order bit in the VC Type field. If the bit is set, it indicates the presence of a control word on this VC. Valid when fec_type is vc. This parameter is always 1, when fec_vc_type is cem, fr_dlci or fr_dlci_rfc4619.
The value of the CEM option. Valid only when -mode is create/modify and -fec_vc_type is cem and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.
If checked, indicates that the CEM option is present. Valid only when -mode is create or modify and -fec_vc_type is cem and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.
The length of the CEM payload (in bytes). Valid only when -mode is create or modify and -fec_vc_type is cem and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.
If checked, indicates that there is a CEM payload. Valid only when -mode is create or modify and -fec_vc_type is cem and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.
This option can be used to set the number of pseudowires to be configured on each LDP VC range. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork API and fec_type is vc.
Configure the FEC type Valid only when using IxTclNetwork API and fec_type is vc. Valid choices are: generalized_id_fec_vpls - Generalized Id FEC 0x81 VPLS pw_id_fec - PW Id FEC 0x80

choice.choiceText: Denotes the Generalized Id FEC 0x81 VPLS.

description.text: A user-defined 32-bit value used to identify a group of VCs. Valid when fec_type is vc.
The 32-bit VC connection identifier. Used with the VC type to identify a specific VC. Valid when fec_type is vc.
The increment step to be added to the VCID to create the next VCID in a group of VCIDs. Valid when fec_type is vc.
(in octets) The 2-octet value for the maximum Transmission Unit (MTU). Valid when fec_type is vc.
An optional user-defined Interface Description. It may be used with ALL VC types. Valid length is 0 to 80 octets. Valid when fec_type is vc.

If fec_vc_mac_range_vlan_enable is 1, this it the number of MAC address/VLAN combinations that will be created. If fec_vc_mac_range_vlan_enable is 0, this is the number of MAC addresses that will be created. Valid only when -mode is create or modify and -fec_vc_type is eth or eth_vlan and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.

If checked, the MAC range corresponding to the layer2 VC range will be enabled. Valid only when -mode is create or modify and -fec_vc_type is eth or eth_vlan and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.
The VLAN ID for the first VLAN in the MAC/VLAN range. Valid only when -mode is create or modify and -fec_vc_type is eth or eth_vlan and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.
The first MAC address in the MAC range. Valid only when -mode is create or modify and -fec_vc_type is eth or eth_vlan and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.
The 32-bit IP address of the LDP Peer. Valid only when -mode is create or modify and fec_type is vc.

The 15-bit VC Type used in the VC FEC element. It depends on the Layer 2 protocol used on the interface. Valid when fec_type is vc. Valid choices are: atm_aal5_vcc - ATM AAL5 VCC transport (VC Type 0x0002) atm_cell - ATM Transparent cell transport (VC Type 0x0003) atm_vcc_1_1 - ATM VCC cell transport (VC Type 0x0009) atm_vcc_n_1 - ATM VCC cell transport (VC Type 0x0009) atm_vpc_1_1 - ATM VPC cell transport (VC Type 0x000A) atm_vpc_n_1 - ATM VPC cell transport (VC Type 0x000A) cem - Circuit Emulation Service over MPLS (CEM), for encapsulation of TDM signal (VC Type 0x8008) eth - untagged Ethernet frames (VC Type 0x0005) eth_vlan - VLAN-tagged Ethernet frames (VC Type 0x0004) eth_vpls - Internet Protocol packets (VC Type 0x000B) fr_dlci - Frame Relay DLCI (VC Type 0x0001) hdlc - HDLC frames (VC Type 0x0006) ppp - Point-to-Point Protocol frames (VC Type 0x0007) satop_e1 - Satop-E1 satop_e3 - Satop-E3 satop_t1 - Satop-T1 satop_t3 - Satop-T3 cesopsn_basic - CESoPSN-Basic cesopsn_cas - CESoPSN-CAS fr_dlci_rfc4619 - RFC 4619 Frame Relay DLCI (VC Type 0x0019)

notes.note:
Coded versus functional specification.
If fec_type option is ipv4_prefix, the label_msg_type option must be mapping; if fec_type option is host_addr, the the label_msg_type option must be request.
For "modify" mode, the fec_type option and label_msg_type option will not be updated for the lsp.
When using the new IxTclNetwork API 5.30, the label_msg_type option is silently ignored. Only the fec_type option is used. If the current session or command was run with -return_detailed_handles 0 the following keys will be omitted from the command response: fecproperty_handles, ipv6_fecproperty_handles, ldppwvpls_handles, ldpotherpws_handles, ldpvplsbgpad_handles
